cards.front:
A farmer has a 150cm tall water trough, that fills at a rate of 10cm per minute. One morning, the water level is 40cm.
How long will it take to fill to capacity?

The materials cost to build something in your engineering firm is $300.00 per cube meter.
A client wants a conical event centre that is 76m at its widest point, and 120m tall. You convince them that nipple-esq buildings aren't in vogue, and chop off the top 30m of the initial design - while quoting the original amount.
How much have you saved in building costs capitalist swine?
